        I_APOLOGIZE_BUT_IT_SEEMS_THAT_YOU_CANNOT                                = 10884,  -- I apologize, but it seems that you cannot visit the Isle yet. I have nothing to say to you.
        THERE_IS_SOMETHING_I_MUST_TELL_THE_ADVENTURERS                          = 10885,  -- There is something I must tell the adventurers of Jeuno! If you could just give me a bit of your time...
        LISTEN_TO_WHAT_HE_HAS_TO_SAY_SURE                                       = 10886,  -- Listen to what he has to say? Sure. Not now.
        WELL_THEN_YOU_MUST_COME_BACK_WHEN_YOU                                   = 10887,  -- Well then, you must come back when you have more time!
        I_BELIEVE_THIS_IS_OUR_FIRST_MEETING                                     = 10888,  -- I believe this is our first meeting.
        I_AM_AFDEEN_PUPIL_OF_THE_GREAT_ABDHALJS                                 = 10889,  -- I am Afdeen, pupil of the great Abdhaljs before even Tillecoe. A pleasure to make your acquaintance.
        THERE_IS_A_REASON_WHY_I_AM_HERE                                         = 10890,  -- There is a reason why I am here. Allow me to explain...
        AN_INTERESTING_IDEA_WAS_PROPOSED_AT_THE_LAST                            = 10891,  -- An interesting idea was proposed at the last Conquest Evaluation Assembly...
        AND_SO_IT_SEEMS_THAT_THE_ADVENTURERS_ARE                                = 10892,  -- ...And so it seems that the adventurers are using their own unique set of rules for Ballista.
        THERE_IS_ALSO_THE_REMARKABLE_NEWS_THAT_THE                              = 10893,  -- There is also the remarkable news that the most capable adventurers in the world came together for a tournament that encompassed the greater part of Vana'diel.
        BALLISTA_HAS_BEEN_TAKEN_OUT_OF_OUR_HANDS                                = 10894,  -- Ballista has been taken out of our hands and placed into those of the adventurers.
        I_AGREE_THE_BALLISTA_PARTICIPANTS_HAVE_FORCED_US                        = 10895,  -- I agree. The Ballista participants have forced us to recall the true meaning of the word hero.
        THE_REVIVAL_OF_BALLISTA_HAS_RAISED_MORALE_AND                           = 10896,  -- The revival of Ballista has raised morale and restored public order. I suppose we have achieved our original goals.
        WE_HAVE_HAVE_WE                                                         = 10897,  -- ...We have, have we?
        IT_CERTAINLY_SOUNDS_LIKE_SOMEONE_S_A_MITE                               = 10898,  -- It certainly sounds like someone's a mite bitter...
        VOLKER_CAN_T_JUST_MUMBLE_AND_GRUMBLE_AT                                 = 10899,  -- Volker can't just mumble and grumble at Destin's baby boy. If you want an explanation, then stop being coy!
        YOU_HAVE_TO_CHARGE_IN_BE_FRANK_AND                                      = 10900,  -- You have to charge in! Be frank and direct. That's the only way to get the response you expect!
        WHAT_DID_YOU_JUST_CALL_ME                                               = 10901,  -- What did you just call me!?
        STOP_QUARRELING_IT_IS_MY_FAULT_FOR_MUMBLING                             = 10902,  -- Stop quarreling! It is my fault for mumbling to myself. Please listen to what I have to say.
        I_AGREE_THAT_THE_SAN_D_ORIAN_ROYAL                                      = 10903,  -- I agree that the San d'Orian Royal Knights are endowed with sound, quick decision-making abilities and deserve admiration.
        THE_DEEDS_OF_A_SINGLE_HERO_ARE_CAPABLE                                  = 10904,  -- The deeds of a single hero are capable of setting afire the hearts of many a soldier. We must not neglect the power of motivation in leading an army to victory.
        EVEN_SO_SOLDIERS_MUST_BE_ABLE_TO_FOLLOW                                 = 10905,  -- Even so, soldiers must be able to follow their commander's orders and fulfill their given roles. Arbitrary decisions can lead an entire army to its doom.
        THUS_I_AM_OF_THE_OPINION_THAT_OBSERVING                                 = 10906,  -- Thus, I am of the opinion that observing Ballista matches in their current state may not be a beneficial practice for our armies.
        YOUR_REMARKS_ARE_INEXCUSABLE_HOW_DARE_YOU_DENOUNCE                      = 10907,  -- Your remarks are inexcusable! How dare you denounce a San d'Orian tradition! I suggest you reconsider your statements.
        I_APOLOGIZE_I_MUST_ADMIT_THAT_BALLISTA_HAS                              = 10908,  -- I apologize. I must admit that Ballista has noticeably improved the skills of many an adventurer and educated our soldiers on the importance of courage.
        HOWEVER_THE_REALITY_IS_THAT_OUR_ARMIES_ARE                              = 10909,  -- However, the reality is that our armies are divided into several units, each with its own role. The soldiers must be able to coordinate themselves effectively and behave as a whole. I believe that a new form of Conflict that trains participants to work in a group would be most rewarding.
        HARUMPH_DO_WE_LOOK_LIKE_CHILDREN_TO_YOU                                 = 10910,  -- Harumph, do we look like children to you? You could have cut that explanation in half and it would have been more than sufficientaru!
        ALL_RIGHT_THEN_I_LL_GET_STRAIGHT_TO                                     = 10911,  -- All right then. I'll get straight to the point now.
        OH_GIVE_US_A_BREAK_WHAT_POINT_COULD                                     = 10912,  -- Oh, give us a break! What point could you make? All your vague statements and whatnot! Why not lend an ear to what I've got?
        NO_THANKS_WELL_THEN_I_SHALL_BE_FRANK                                    = 10913,  -- No thanks... Well then, I shall be frank.
        I_PROPOSE_THE_REINSTATEMENT_OF_BRENNER_AS_A                             = 10914,  -- I propose the reinstatement of Brenner as a new form of Conflict!
        BRENNER                                                                 = 10915,  -- Brenner!?
        I_REMEMBER_THAT_NAME_BEFORE_THE_GREAT_WAR                               = 10916,  -- I remember that name. Before the Great War, Brenner was used in the selection of the Gold Musketeers. However, the competition was extraordinarily fierce, and it is said that the casualties always exceeded the number of successful candidates.
        THOSE_STORIES_WERE_FABRICATED_SIMPLY_TO_EXAGGERATE_THE                  = 10917,  -- Those stories were fabricated simply to exaggerate the danger of Brenner.
        BRENNER_WAS_ORIGINALLY_CREATED_AS_A_TRAINING_EXERCISE                   = 10918,  -- Brenner was originally created as a training exercise for mineworkers. The outcome of each match relied on the participants' skill in role management and encouraged team competition.
        OF_COURSE_I_AM_NOT_SUGGESTING_THAT_WE                                   = 10919,  -- Of course, I am not suggesting that we abolish Ballista. I simply advise that we add Brenner to the list of training options in order to supply the elements of teamwork that I find lacking in current matches.
        HMPH_SO_YOU_WISH_TO_FORTIFY_YOUR_ARMY                                   = 10920,  -- Hmph, so you wish to fortify your army by tying them tightly together in iron bonds. How very-wery Bastokan!
        OHOHOHO_STILL_THE_IDEA_MAKES_MY_HEART_RACE                              = 10921,  -- Ohohoho! Still, the idea makes my heart race! I even support it. You make a good case!
        OHOHOHO_SO_IF_YOUR_WEAKLINGS_UNITE_YOU_THINK                            = 10922,  -- Ohohoho! So if your weaklings unite, you think you can win any fight?
        OHO_THIS_IS_RICH_MAY_YOUR_PLAN_GO                                       = 10923,  -- Oho, this is rich! May your plan go without hitch!
        I_WILL_SUPPORT_YOUR_PLAN_BUT_PLEASE_BE                                  = 10924,  -- I will support your plan, but please be aware that against the black mages, no one's got a prayer!
        IF_IT_WILL_SUPPLEMENT_BALLISTA_I_BELIEVE_THAT                           = 10925,  -- If it will supplement Ballista, I believe that even Excenmille would have no argument. You have my approval.
        I_APPRECIATE_YOUR_DECISION_NOW_I_ALSO_WOULD                             = 10926,  -- I appreciate your decision. Now I also would like to suggest that we do away with the license requirement and nationality restrictions for Brenner.
        QUITE_A_BOLD_STATEMENT_HOWEVER_TEAMS_WOULD_BE                           = 10927,  -- Quite a bold statement. However, teams would be composed of complete strangers if we enforce what you propose. Is that your desire?
        THE_ADVENTURERS_HAVE_TAUGHT_ME_MUCH_BUT_ONE                             = 10928,  -- The adventurers have taught me much, but one of the greatest lessons I have learned is the strength of the bond between linkshell members.
        LINKSHELLS_PROVIDE_AN_EXEMPLARY_MODEL_OF_UNITY_THE                      = 10929,  -- Linkshells provide an exemplary model of unity. The cooperation and friendly competition of these groups are like those of the closest companions or even family. And thus, I propose that we introduce matches divided by linkshell rather than nation.
        INTERESTING_YOU_SEEM_TO_HAVE_WORKED_OUT_THESE                           = 10930,  -- Interesting. You seem to have worked out these plans more thoroughly than I expected. Have you also given consideration to where the matches will be held?
        OF_COURSE_WOLFGANG_SHALL_WE_INVITE_OUR_GUEST                            = 10931,  -- Of course. Wolfgang, shall we invite our guest in now?
        A_PLEASURE_TO_MAKE_YOUR_ACQUAINTANCE_I_AM                               = 10932,  -- A pleasure to make your acquaintance. I am called Afdeen.
        I_HAVE_COME_TO_YOUR_LANDS_BY_ORDER                                      = 10933,  -- I have come to your lands by order of the great Abdhaljs.
        BY_ALTANA_DO_YOU_MEAN_TO_SUGGEST_THAT                                   = 10934,  -- By Altana! Do you mean to suggest that you are a direct disciple of Sir Abdhaljs? I believe I have heard your name before.
        IS_YOUR_MASTER_IN_GOOD_HEALTH_HE_DESERVES                               = 10935,  -- Is your master in good health? He deserves our gratitude for the Diorama...
        YES_HE_IS_QUITE_WELL_HOWEVER_HE_DESIRES                                 = 10936,  -- Yes, he is quite well. However, he desires no reward. He is quite pleased with the Ballista matches that take place each day in the Diorama.
        ON_ANOTHER_NOTE_HE_HAS_EXPRESSED_INTEREST_IN                            = 10937,  -- On another note, he has expressed interest in a new form of Conflict. He has entrusted me with matters regarding his new diorama, which is designed after Purgonorgo Isle.
        THE_GREAT_ABDHALJS_HAS_CREATED_A_NEW_DIORAMA                            = 10938,  -- The great Abdhaljs has created a new diorama specifically for this new form of Conflict? Magnificent! You will hear no argument from me.
        THAT_S_DANDY_WANDY_BUT_DON_T_FORGET                                     = 10939,  -- That's dandy-wandy, but don't forget that Windurst won't lend a single gil to the project!
        WELL_THERE_YOU_HAVE_IT_THE_PREPARATIONS_SOUND                           = 10940,  -- Well, there you have it. The preparations sound fine! Okay then, inform me when Windurst is next in line!
        THE_REINSTATEMENT_OF_BRENNER_HAS_NOW_BEEN_APPROVED                      = 10941,  -- The reinstatement of Brenner has now been approved!
        I_WILL_SEND_A_DETAILED_EXPLANATION_OF_THE                               = 10942,  -- I will send a detailed explanation of the rules to each of you. If you should have any objections, please take them up with Sir Wolfgang.
        OBVIOUSLY_THE_CITIZENS_OF_WINDURST_HAVE_THE_CLOSESTARU                  = 10943,  -- Obviously, the citizens of Windurst have the closestaru bond. Our adventurers will have to teach the rest of you a thing or two about teamwork now.
        I_AM_SIMPLY_BESIDE_MYSELF_MY_PRAYERS_WILL                               = 10944,  -- I am simply beside myself--my prayers will not cease! Wishing your people get through this in one piece! Ohohoho`!
        I_WILL_NOT_STAND_FOR_THESE_MEANINGLESS_INSULTS                          = 10945,  -- I will not stand for these meaningless insults against the Royal Knights! Our records in Ballista prove our prowess in working as a team.
        I_THINK_IT_IS_TIME_TO_CALL_THIS                                         = 10946,  -- I think it is time to call this meeting to a close. Thank you all for your participation.
        HOW_CAN_ANY_IDEA_BE_INTERESTING_WHEN_BASTOK                             = 10947,  -- How can any idea be interesting when Bastok thoughtaru of it first?
        YOU_RE_MISSING_THE_POINT_THIS_LL_MAKE                                   = 10948,  -- You're missing the point--this'll make them prepared for the time that they're needed, my plans unimpaired!
        YOUR_PLANS_YOU_CAN_T_MEAN                                               = 10949,  -- Your plans? You can't mean...
        NOW_TO_JUST_WAIT_AND_SEE_WHAT_BRENNER                                   = 10950,  -- Now to just wait and see what Brenner will bring to me!
        I_LL_NEED_MANY_A_STRONG_ADVENTURER_FOR                                  = 10951,  -- I'll need many a strong adventurer for my grand plans, that's for sure! Ohohoho!
        SENDING_AJIDO_MARUJIDO_TO_THE_ASSEMBLY_HAD_RESULTS                      = 10952,  -- Sending Ajido-Marujido to the assembly had results most intriguing. They actually helped me save time for my scheming!
