        NOW_THAT_S_SOMETHING_TO_GET_YOUR_HEART                                  = 13219,  -- Now that's something to get your heart pumping! A trial and a job all in one!? So, I get to thrash the dirty hides of fiendish brutes for money? Lace my boots and call me ready!
        I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THIS_MOTIVATED_IN_A                                      = 13220,  -- I haven't seen [Feliz/Ferdinand/Gunnar/Massimo/Oldrich/Siegward/Theobald/Zenji] this motivated in a long time. Be surrre to use that to your advantage.
        I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THIS_MOTIVATED_IN_A_2                                    = 13221,  -- I haven't seen [Amerita/Beatrice/Henrietta/Jesimae/Karyn/Nanako/Sharlene/Sieghilde] this motivated in a long time. Be surrre to use that to your advantage.
        I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THIS_MOTIVATED_IN_A_3                                    = 13222,  -- I haven't seen [Chanandit/Deulmaeux/Demresinaux/Ephealgaux/Gauldeval/Grauffemart/Migaifongut/Romidiant] this motivated in a long time. Make surrre you use that to your advantage.
        I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THIS_MOTIVATED_IN_A_4                                    = 13223,  -- I haven't seen [Armittie/Cadepure/Clearite/Epilleve/Liabelle/Nauthima/Radille/Vimechue] this motivated in a long time. Be surrre to use that to your advantage.
        I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THIS_MOTIVATED_IN_A_5                                    = 13224,  -- I haven't seen [Balu-Falu/Burg-Ladarg/Ehgo-Ryuhgo/Kolui-Pelui/Nokum-Akkum/Savul-Kivul/Vinja-Kanja/Yarga-Umiga] this motivated in a long time. Be surrre to use that to your advantage.
        I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THIS_MOTIVATED_IN_A_6                                    = 13225,  -- I haven't seen [Cupapa/Jajuju/Kalokoko/Mahoyaya/Pakurara/Ripokeke/Yawawa/Yufafa] this motivated in a long time. Be surrre to use that to your advantage.
        I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THIS_MOTIVATED_IN_A_7                                    = 13226,  -- I haven't seen [Fhig Lahry/Khuma Tagyawhan/Pimy Kettihl/Raka Maimhov/Sahyu Banjyao/Sufhi Uchnouma/Tsuim Nhomango/Yoli Kohlpaka] this motivated in a long time. Be surrre to use that to your advantage.
        I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THIS_MOTIVATED_IN_A_8                                    = 13227,  -- I haven't seen [Durib/Dzapiwa/Jugowa/Mugido/Voldai/Wagwei/Zayag/Zoldof] this motivated in a long time. Be surrre to use that to your advantage.
        ANYWAY_JUST_IN_CASE_YOUR_ATTENTION_SPAN_S                               = 13228,  -- Anyway, just in case your attention span's shorrrter than my supply of catnip, bring me % when you're done with the trial. Get it? Got it? Good.
        BE_CAREFUL_OUT_THERE_AND_TEARRR_EM_ALL                                  = 13229,  -- Be careful out there...and tearrr 'em all to shreds!
        CONGRATULATIONS_ON_FINISHING_WITH_YOUR_NINE_LIVES_INTACT                = 13230,  -- Congratulations on finishing with your nine lives intact. I see you also remembered to bring back % . Grrreat job! So, how'd it feel working for the Man--er, Mithra?
        IT_WAS_REFRESHING_TO_FEEL_SOMETHING_OTHER_THAN                          = 13231,  -- It was refreshing to feel something other than frustration at this eternal struggle for self-betterment. I guess it was nice to have been of service, too.
        JUST_THE_SIGHT_OF_AND_ME_WAS_SO                                         = 13232,  -- Just the sight of % and me was so imposing that they cowered and ran away without a fight! Next time, could you give us something a little more meaty and flavorful?
        PFFFT_I_COULD_VE_GOTTEN_A_WAGONFUL_OF                                   = 13233,  -- Pffft. I could've gotten a wagonful of those things without a problem. I don't know if I could even call what we just did work.
        IT_WAS_A_VALUABLE_LEARNING_EXPERIENCE_IT_WILL                           = 13234,  -- It was a valuable learning experience. It will also be liberating to finally not have to rely on my parents for pecuniary aid.
        WHY_D_YOU_GIVE_US_SUCH_AN_EASY                                          = 13235,  -- Why'd you give us such an easy job with barely any clashing, bashing, or mashing? Don't think you can coddle me just 'cause I called you my big sister once!
        THAT_WAS_A_NICE_BIT_OF_EXERCISE_MY                                      = 13236,  -- That was a nice bit of exercise. My muscles are rippling even more than when we set out. Fighting beside % was all fine and well, but how about you and I meet for a midnight spar sometime, Luto?
        THANK_YOU_FOR_ASKING_LUTO_WELL_KNOWING_I                                = 13237,  -- Thank you for asking, Luto! Well, knowing I contributed to society this time has given me an even more powerful sense of accomplishment! Without a doubt, I'll be sleeping soundly tonight.
        I_M_SO_WORKED_UP_I_CAN_T                                                = 13238,  -- I'm so worked up I can't even describe how I feel! I was all like, Boom, Hya, Shaaa, the whole time! I haven't felt like this in sooo long!
        IT_WAS_BOTH_A_PLEASURE_AND_AN_HONOR                                     = 13239,  -- It was both a pleasure and an honor to successfully execute such a significant assignment with %. That alone is enough of a reward, and yet I was blessed with this new feeling of empowerment as well. I simply could not be any happier.
        IT_S_LIKE_I_DOUBLED_MY_TREASURE_DOUBLED                                 = 13240,  -- It's like I doubled my treasure, doubled my fun, and doubled my power with...ummm, how's that go again?
        IT_WAS_AN_INVALUABLE_EXPERIENCE_AND_A_WONDERFUL                         = 13241,  -- It was an invaluable experience and a wonderful opportunity to improve not only my own, but someone else's life as well. I thank you for giving me such a chance, Luto.
        OH_THE_RUSH_YOU_WOULDN_T_BELIEVE_IT                                     = 13242,  -- Oh, the rush! You wouldn't believe it! I've never felt so alive as when I was killing monsters...for the sake of others! I'm eternally indebted to you, Luto.
        GLAD_TO_SEE_YOU_GRRRABBED_THIS_JOB_BY                                   = 13243,  -- Glad to see you grrrabbed this job by the throat and shook the life out of it. Hopefully that enthusiasm will lead to more work sometime soon. All we can do now though is wait and see.
        I_CAN_T_TELL_IF_SHE_S_THE                                               = 13244,  -- ...I can't tell if she's the most violent and deranged Mithra I've met or she's just overly excitable. At any rate, I'm getting out of here. Stay alive, %.
        AS_MUCH_AS_I_WOULD_LIKE_TO_REST                                         = 13245,  -- As much as I would like to rest on my laurels, %, I can't ignore the call of natu--er, adventure. To the herocave!
        INDEED_I_GUESS_I_SHOULD_GET_BACK_TO                                     = 13246,  -- Indeed. I guess I should get back to my daily routine of doing amazing things in exotic locales with famous people. Until next time, %.
        I_EAGERLY_AWAIT_OUR_NEXT_ASSIGNMENT_I_SHALL                             = 13247,  -- I eagerly await our next assignment. I shall now return to my parents' humble abode and bide my time until I am needed once more. Until we meet again, %.
        THAT_S_MY_MENTOR_I_BET_YOU_ALREADY                                      = 13248,  -- That's my mentor! I bet you already have something lined up--wait a minute! You're holding out on me just to be a big meanie bully, aren't you!? Make sure she doesn't run away, %! I'm gonna go tell on her!
        THAT_S_RIGHT_LUTO_YOU_KNOW_EXACTLY_HOW                                  = 13249,  -- That's right, Luto. You know exactly how to make this tomcat purr. And if you're ready to accept that offer, you know where to find me. Alright, %, if you ever need help gettin' in with the ladies/gentlemen], just give me a holler.
        MAY_THAT_TIME_COME_SOONER_RATHER_THAN_LATER                             = 13250,  -- May that time come sooner rather than later. I wouldn't want to leave my dear % all by his/her] lonesome for too long. Anyway, I would love to stay and chat, but I can hear my household chores calling me. Ta-ta, you two!
        YEAH_THAT_D_BE_FABUWONDEROUS_IF_WE_GOT                                  = 13251,  -- Yeah, that'd be fabuwonderous if we got another gig! We'd be all, Look at us with our money and our skills! We're the besterrific! Oh, whoa! ItotallyforgotI'vegottogonow! Bye, %!
        I_WOULD_BE_EXTREMELY_APPRECIATIVE_WERE_YOU_TO                           = 13252,  -- I would be extremely appreciative were you to inform me the moment we receive a new job offer, Luto. I enjoyed this excursion so much, I simply cannot wait to go on another! And %, if you need anything--anything at all--please do not hesitate to contact me.
        LUTO_DON_T_SAY_THAT_IN_FRONT_OF                                         = 13253,  -- Luto, don't say that in front of me! It's disgusting! Uh, I mean the throat-shaking thing, not the getting-another-job thing! I'd love another chance to help a fellow citizen in need! Anywho, bye-byebees, %!
        I_SHALL_STAY_EVER_VIGILANT_UNTIL_THAT_TIME                              = 13254,  -- I shall stay ever vigilant until that time--eyes peeled, searching for denizens in need. Should you wish to accompany me, %, dally not long, for evil never rests!
        I_LIKE_YOUR_STYLE_LUTO_THAT_S_THE                                       = 13255,  -- I like your style, Luto! That's the same way I would've put it, except maybe with a bit more blood and leather. Hahaha! %, if you ever have some down time and need to get whipped back into shape, you know where to find me.
        NOW_THAT_THOSE_RUNTS_HAVE_RUN_BACK_TO                                   = 13256,  -- Now that those runts have run back to their litter, I just need to rrrelay these % to our client and collect my pay.
        WHAT_UM_AHEM_I_MEAN_OUR_PAY_OF                                          = 13257,  -- ...What!? Um, ahem, I mean our pay, of course! Serrriously, %, if you've got enough time to eavesdrop on honest, harrrdworking folk, why don't you make yourself useful and go on another adventure with [Feliz/Ferdinand/Gunnar/Massimo/Oldrich/Siegward/Theobald/Zenji]!?
        WHAT_UM_AHEM_I_MEAN_OUR_PAY_OF_2                                        = 13258,  -- ...What!? Um, ahem, I mean our pay, of course! Serrriously, %, if you've got enough time to eavesdrop on honest, harrrdworking folk, why don't you make yourself useful and go on another adventure with [Amerita/Beatrice/Henrietta/Jesimae/Karyn/Nanako/Sharlene/Sieghilde]!?
        WHAT_UM_AHEM_I_MEAN_OUR_PAY_OF_3                                        = 13259,  -- ...What!? Um, ahem, I mean our pay, of course! Serrriously, %, if you've got enough time to eavesdrop on honest, harrrdworking folk, why don't you make yourself useful and go on another adventure with [Chanandit/Deulmaeux/Demresinaux/Ephealgaux/Gauldeval/Grauffemart/Migaifongut/Romidiant]!?
        WHAT_UM_AHEM_I_MEAN_OUR_PAY_OF_4                                        = 13260,  -- ...What!? Um, ahem, I mean our pay, of course! Serrriously, %, if you've got enough time to eavesdrop on honest, harrrdworking folk, why don't you make yourself useful and go on another adventure with [Armittie/Cadepure/Clearite/Epilleve/Liabelle/Nauthima/Radille/Vimechue]!?
        WHAT_UM_AHEM_I_MEAN_OUR_PAY_OF_5                                        = 13261,  -- ...What!? Um, ahem, I mean our pay, of course! Serrriously, %, if you've got enough time to eavesdrop on honest, harrrdworking folk, why don't you make yourself useful and go on another adventure with [Balu-Falu/Burg-Ladarg/Ehgo-Ryuhgo/Kolui-Pelui/Nokum-Akkum/Savul-Kivul/Vinja-Kanja/Yarga-Umiga]!?
        WHAT_UM_AHEM_I_MEAN_OUR_PAY_OF_6                                        = 13262,  -- ...What!? Um, ahem, I mean our pay, of course! Serrriously, %, if you've got enough time to eavesdrop on honest, harrrdworking folk, why don't you make yourself useful and go on another adventure with [Cupapa/Jajuju/Kalokoko/Mahoyaya/Pakurara/Ripokeke/Yawawa/Yufafa]!?
        WHAT_UM_AHEM_I_MEAN_OUR_PAY_OF_7                                        = 13263,  -- ...What!? Um, ahem, I mean our pay, of course! Serrriously, %, if you've got enough time to eavesdrop on honest, harrrdworking folk, why don't you make yourself useful and go on another adventure with [Fhig Lahry/Khuma Tagyawhan/Pimy Kettihl/Raka Maimhov/Sahyu Banjyao/Sufhi Uchnouma/Tsuim Nhomango/Yoli Kohlpaka]!?
        WHAT_UM_AHEM_I_MEAN_OUR_PAY_OF_8                                        = 13264,  -- ...What!? Um, ahem, I mean our pay, of course! Serrriously, %, if you've got enough time to eavesdrop on honest, harrrdworking folk, why don't you make yourself useful and go on another adventure with [Durib/Dzapiwa/Jugowa/Mugido/Voldai/Wagwei/Zayag/Zoldof]!?
        YOU_TWO_MAY_THINK_YOU_RE_THE_CAT                                        = 13265,  -- You two may think you're the cat's shalwars, but you're hardly strrrong enough to bite the hand that feeds you. Maybe you will be eventually if you keep training, but until then, you shouldn't get too full of yourselves.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_MHMU_S_PORTER_SERVICE_KUPO                               = 13266,  -- Welcome to the MHMU's porter service, kupo! Which of your burdensome belongings shall I take off your hands today?
        DO_SOMETHING_KUPO_PORTER_SERVICE_BUY_A_STORAGE                          = 13267,  -- Do something, kupo? Porter service? Buy a storage slip. No, thank you.
        IS_YOUR_GOBBIEBAG_SPLITTING_AT_THE_SEAMS_MOG                            = 13268,  -- Is your gobbiebag splitting at the seams? Mog Safe spilling over? Why, an accomplished adventurer like yourself surely has more stuff than you know what to do with.
        THAT_S_WHERE_I_COME_IN_KUPO_I                                           = 13269,  -- That's where I come in, kupo. I'll gladly hold onto your prized possessions, freeing you space to gather up even grander goodies.
        TO_MAKE_USE_OF_MY_SERVICES_FIRST_YOU                                    = 13270,  -- To make use of my services, first you'll need to buy one of these storage slips for the low, low fee of # gil.
        STORAGE_SLIPS_COME_IN_NUMEROUS_VARIETIES_KUPO_EACH                      = 13271,  -- Storage slips come in numerous varieties, kupo, each corresponding to a different type of item.
        YOU_LL_WANT_TO_PERUSE_THE_FINE_PRINT                                    = 13272,  -- You'll want to peruse the fine print closely, so you don't end up paying good gil for a scrap of parchment useless for the particular item you wish to store.
        NOT_THAT_WE_MOOGLES_WOULD_OBJECT_TO_THAT                                = 13273,  -- Not that we moogles would object to that sort of donation, kupo.
        CHOOSE_THE_ITEM_YOU_WISH_TO_ENTRUST_THEN                                = 13274,  -- Choose the item you wish to entrust, then trade it to me along with a single storage slip. I will take the item and return the slip to you, marked with an invisible seal.
        INVISIBLE_TO_YOU_AT_LEAST_IT_S_PLAIN                                    = 13275,  -- Invisible to you, at least. It's plain as day to us moogles, so don't even think of trying to pull one over on us, kupo.
        WHEN_IT_COMES_TIME_TO_RETRIEVE_YOUR_ITEM                                = 13276,  -- When it comes time to retrieve your item, just trade to me a single storage slip--any slip--once again.
        I_WILL_PRESENT_YOU_WITH_A_LIST_OF                                       = 13277,  -- I will present you with a list of all the items currently in my care, and you may choose the one you wish to withdraw. Simple as that, kupo!
        WHAT_S_MORE_NO_ADDITIONAL_TRANSACTION_FEES_WILL                         = 13278,  -- What's more, no additional transaction fees will be incurred! Pretty generous of us for a change, no?
        NOW_I_BET_YOU_RE_WONDERING_WHAT_THE                                     = 13279,  -- Now I bet you're wondering what the catch is, kupo. So as not to disappoint you, there are a few!
        FOR_ONE_ANY_SIGNED_ITEMS_WILL_LOSE_THEIR                                = 13280,  -- For one, any signed items will lose their signatures if you store them with me.
        WHY_YOU_SAY_HEY_EVEN_WE_MOOGLES_AREN                                    = 13281,  -- Why, you say? Hey, even we moogles aren't perfect! It's better for both of us if you keep your most precious possessions close at hand, kupo.
        NOW_LISTEN_UP_BECAUSE_THERE_S_ANOTHER_CATCH                             = 13282,  -- Now listen up, because there's another catch, and it's a doozy.
        IF_YOU_LOSE_YOUR_STORAGE_SLIP_I_WON                                     = 13283,  -- If you lose your storage slip, I won't be able to return your item. Ever. No ifs, ands, or buts! No I'm sorry, Mister Porter Moogle, it'll never happen again! Rules are rules, kupo, and someone has to keep them.
        LAST_BUT_NOT_LEAST_I_CAN_T_ACCEPT                                       = 13284,  -- Last, but not least, I can't accept equipment bearing Magian trial insignia.
        IF_YOU_HAVE_SUCH_AN_ITEM_THAT_YOU                                       = 13285,  -- If you have such an item that you're simply dying to entrust to me, you'll have to abandon your trial first, kupo.
        AND_THAT_S_ALL_THERE_IS_TO_IT                                           = 13286,  -- And that's all there is to it. This humble moogle can hardly wait to serve you!
        BUY_SOMETHING_P_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE_CANCEL                          = 13287,  -- Buy something? (p. #/#). Previous page. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Next page. Cancel.
        WILL_COST_YOU_GIL_DO_WE_HAVE_A                                          = 13288,  -- % will cost you # gil. Do we have a deal, kupo?
        DEAL_KUPO_CURRENT_GIL_CHECK_STORABLE_ITEMS_DEAL                         = 13289,  -- Deal, kupo? (Current gil: #). Check storable items. Deal. No deal.
        THE_WILL_ALLOW_YOU_TO_STORE_THE_FOLLOWING                               = 13290,  -- The % will allow you to store the following items:
        ID_13291                                                                = 13291,  -- %.
        ID_13292                                                                = 13292,  -- %.
        AND_THAT_S_ALL                                                          = 13293,  -- ...and that's all.
        P_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE_CANCEL                                        = 13294,  -- % (p. #/#). Previous page. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Next page. Cancel.
        WARNING_IF_YOU_LOSE_YOUR_WHILE_STORING_A                                = 13295,  -- Warning! If you lose your % while storing a corresponding item, you will be forever unable to retrieve that item!
        IS_THAT_I_SEE_KUPO                                                      = 13296,  -- Is that % I see, kupo?
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_RETRIEVE_AN_ITEM_CONFIRM                               = 13297,  -- What will you do? Retrieve an item. Confirm storable items. Nothing.
        RETRIEVE_AN_ITEM_P_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE                              = 13298,  -- Retrieve an item? (p. #/#). Previous page. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Next page. Cancel.
        RETRIEVE_RETRIEVE_IT_LEAVE_IT                                           = 13299,  -- Retrieve %? Retrieve it. Leave it.
        YOU_RETRIEVE_FROM_THE_PORTER_MOOGLE_S_CARE                              = 13300,  -- You retrieve % from the porter moogle's care.
        KUPO_I_M_ALREADY_TAKING_CARE_OF_THAT                                    = 13301,  -- Kupo? I'm already taking care of that item for you.
        YES_VERY_WELL_YOUR_PRECIOUS_PROPERTY_IS_SAFE                            = 13302,  -- %, yes? Very well! Your precious property is safe with me, kupo!
        OF_ITEM_IS_IT_VERY_WELL_YOUR_PRECIOUS                                   = 13303,  -- # [variety/varieties] of item, is it? Very well! Your precious property is safe with me, kupo!
        IS_THAT_A_MAGIAN_INSIGNIA_I_SEE_ON                                      = 13304,  -- Is that a Magian insignia I see on that %? You'll have to abandon your trial before I can take it off your hands, kupo.
        THAT_APPEARS_TO_BE_AUGMENTED_I_M_SORRY                                  = 13305,  -- That % appears to be augmented. I'm sorry, but I can't accept such specialized gear, kupo.
        CURIOUS_AS_TO_WHETHER_I_CAN_ACCEPT_THAT                                 = 13306,  -- Curious as to whether I can accept that item? Let me check my annals.
        WHY_YES_I_CAN_CAN_BE_STORED_WITH                                        = 13307,  -- Why, yes I can! % can be stored with %.
        WHY_IT_LOOKS_AS_IF_YOU_HAVE_LOCATED                                     = 13308,  -- Why, it looks as if you have % located in your [inventory/Mog Safe/Mog Safe 2/Mog House storage/Mog Locker/Mog Satchel/Mog Sack/Mog Case/Mog Wardrobe/Mog Wardrobe 2/Mog Wardrobe 3/Mog Wardrobe 4/Mog Wardrobe 5/Mog Wardrobe 6/Mog Wardrobe 7/Mog Wardrobe 8/Recycle Bin]!
        STORABLE_ITEM                                                           = 13309,  -- Storable item: % (#)
        STORABLE_ITEM_2                                                         = 13310,  -- Storable item: % (#)
        ID_0_1_2_3                                                              = 13311,  -- 0: # 1: # 2: # 3: #
        ID_4_5_6_7                                                              = 13312,  -- 4: # 5: # 6: # 7: #
        NO_ID                                                                   = 13313,  -- no: # id: #
        NO_ID_RES                                                               = 13314,  -- no: # id: # res: #
        TB                                                                      = 13315,  -- TB: #
        NPC_INDEX_OUT_OF_RANGE                                                  = 13316,  -- NPC index out of range.
        ERROR_CODE                                                              = 13317,  -- ERROR CODE: # / #
        HMMM_SORRY_BUT_I_DON_T_THINK_YOU                                        = 13318,  -- Hmmm. Sorry, but I don't think you have what it takes to survive these underground caverns.
        HAVE_YOU_HEARD_OF_THE_MEEBLES_BEFORE                                    = 13319,  -- Have you heard of the Meebles before?
        THEY_RE_A_SUBTERRANEAN_RACE_OF_BEASTMEN_THAT                            = 13320,  -- They're a subterranean race of beastmen that strikingly resemble moles. No need to get your britches in a bunch if you haven't, though--studying them is our job.
        WE_THE_MEEBLE_BURROWS_EXPLORATION_COMMITTEE_HAVE_LEFT                   = 13321,  -- We, the Meeble Burrows Exploration Committee, have left no stone--figurative or real--unturned in our search for answers about this elusive species. Our results suggest that Meebles are rather docile creatures, with little if any culture to speak of. They shouldn't pose much of a threat.
        THEY_RE_EASILY_MANIPULATED_THOUGH_AND_THE_MOBLINS                       = 13322,  -- They're easily manipulated, though, and the Moblins have taken advantage of that. They put the Meebles to work throughout a network of burrows.
        MEEBLE_BURROWS_MAY_BE_A_QUAINT_NAME_BUT                                 = 13323,  -- Meeble Burrows may be a quaint name, but what sort of fiends lurk amongst these dank caverns? Why are the Moblins making Meebles do their dirty work? And how large are these underground tunnels anyway? Maybe we haven't learned as much about the Meebles and their habitat as we thought...
        WAIT_IF_YOU_DON_T_MIND_CRAWLING_THROUGH                                 = 13324,  -- Wait...if you don't mind crawling through caves and dirtying your own hands for a good cause, how about joining in the exploration? We could use another pair of eyes down there. Just talk to me when you decide you'd like to help the scientific community.
        OHO_I_KNEW_IT_WAS_A_GOOD_IDEA                                           = 13325,  -- Oho, I knew it was a good idea to prepare this grimoire. Here, it should help with your research.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_CAN_T_CARRY_ANY                                       = 13326,  -- It looks like you can't carry any more. Try emptying some articles out and return when you have the room.
        HAHAHA_YOU_LOOK_LIKE_YOU_VE_JUST_BEEN                                   = 13327,  -- Hahaha, you look like you've just been thrown from a chocobo! No need to be scared. I'll explain the process as best I can, but feel free to ask if I've missed something.
        LET_S_SEE_IF_I_CAN_DO_THIS                                              = 13328,  -- Let's see if I can do this. First, form a party of one to six people. Next, trade your grimoire to the Burrow Researcher in charge of the burrows you're investigating.
        IF_THE_NEED_ARISES_I_CAN_ALWAYS_TRANSPORT                               = 13329,  -- If the need arises, I can always transport you there.
        ALRIGHT_HERE_GOES_NOTHING_FIRST_FORM_A_PARTY                            = 13330,  -- Alright, here goes nothing. First, form a party of one to six people. Next, trade your grimoire to me.
        AND_ONCE_YOU_HAND_IT_OVER_AFTER_THAT                                    = 13331,  -- [You'll receive/I'll give you/I'll give you] % and % once you hand it over. After that's done, you're ready to go spelunking...unless you're the party leader.
        THEN_YOU_LL_HAVE_TO_TALK_TO_AGAIN                                       = 13332,  -- Then you'll have to talk to [the Burrow Researcher/me/me] again to decide which expedition to undertake.
        I_MUST_WARN_YOU_THOUGH_THAT_SOME_EXPEDITIONS                            = 13333,  -- I must warn you, though, that some expeditions require everyone to make a unanimous decision.
        ONCE_YOUR_PARTY_S_EXPEDITION_HAS_BEEN_CHOSEN                            = 13334,  -- Once your party's expedition has been chosen, it's time to go spelunking.
        HAVE_YOUR_PARTY_LEADER_TALK_TO_THE_MEEBLE                               = 13335,  -- Have your party leader talk to the Meeble guarding the burrow entrance. He'll escort you to the right research site.
        AFTER_YOU_VE_FINISHED_AN_EXPEDITION_USE_TO                              = 13336,  -- After you've finished an expedition, use % to return aboveground and report to [the Burrow Researcher in charge or me/me/me] to get your grimoire back.
        NOW_FOR_A_WORD_ABOUT_GRIMOIRES_THEY_IMPART                              = 13337,  -- Now for a word about grimoires. They impart various benefits depending on what expeditions you've completed.
        IT_S_DANGEROUS_DOWN_THERE_SO_BE_SURE                                    = 13338,  -- It's dangerous down there, so be sure to make use of your grimoire.
        FINALLY_WHILE_THERE_ARE_MANY_TYPES_OF_GRIMOIRES                         = 13339,  -- Finally, while there are many types of grimoires, they all share the same attributes. Feel free to change them out depending on your companions and the research assignment at hand.
        YOU_MUST_BE_THE_EXPLORER_MY_COMPATRIOT_IN                               = 13340,  -- You must be the explorer my compatriot in Jeuno was talking about. What brings you here?
        WELL_WELL_LOOK_WHO_IT_IS_WHAT_DO                                        = 13341,  -- Well, well, look who it is. What do you need this time?
        FINALLY_I_VE_BEEN_WAITING_FOR_YOU_THIS                                  = 13342,  -- Finally! I've been waiting for you this whole time.
        WE_THOUGHT_WE_HAD_A_BEAD_ON_THE                                         = 13343,  -- We thought we had a bead on the Meebles' habitat, but it turns out we were dead wrong. There's another set of caverns in the vicinity of Batallia Downs!
        I_CAN_T_UNDERSTAND_HOW_IT_REMAINED_BURIED                               = 13344,  -- I can't understand how it remained buried for so long. Reports abound that the Moblins have expanded their base of operations and are employing Meebles for nefarious deeds once again.
        NOW_IT_S_UP_TO_US_THE_MEEBLE                                            = 13345,  -- Now it's up to us, the Meeble Burrows Exploration Committee, to unearth heaping amounts of knowledge for our glorious archives! Oh, and maybe to save the day, too.
        HOW_YOU_ASK_BY_COLLECTING_AS_MUCH_INFORMATION                           = 13346,  -- How, you ask? By collecting as much information as possible through new expeditions and finally getting to the bottom of this Moblin nuisance! We're always in need of proven researchers like yourself, should you wish to join in the action.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_DO_HEAD_TO                                          = 13347,  -- What do you want to do? Head to the burrows. Choose an expedition. Get my grimoire back. Examine grimoire records. Check % stock. Redeem research marks. Inscribe feats upon your grimoire. Purchase emblems of valiance. Purchase a grimoire. Ask for further information. Review expedition specifics. Nothing for the nonce.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_DO_HEAD_TO_2                                        = 13348,  -- What do you want to do? Head to the burrows. Change expedition. (Currently: [Adj./Ast./Inst./Assoc./Res./R.E.][ #1/ #2/ #3/ #4/ #5/]) Get my grimoire back. Examine grimoire records. Check % stock. Redeem research marks. Inscribe feats upon your grimoire. Purchase emblems of valiance. Purchase a grimoire. Ask for further information. Review expedition specifics. Nothing for the nonce.
        ANY_QUESTIONS_NO_NOT_RIGHT_NOW_HOW_DOES                                 = 13349,  -- Any questions? No, not right now. How does this whole research thing work? I...descend into underground caves!? What are these grimoires about? How do I begin an expedition? What goes on after an expedition? What dastardly foes lurk down below? Any rhyme or reason to these burrows? What are research marks? Can you tell me about the Meebles? What is grimoire engraving? Could you tell me about wizened worms? Palimpsests? Huh?
        YOU_ADVENTURERS_CAN_HELP_US_COLLECT_DATA_BY                             = 13350,  -- You adventurers can help us collect data by embarking on certain expeditions belowground. The goals and activities for each journey you undertake will vary, so this won't be just some routine experiment.
        ALTHOUGH_THESE_SUBTERRANEAN_CAVERNS_MAY_APPEAR_SIMPLISTIC_FROM          = 13351,  -- Although these subterranean caverns may appear simplistic from the outside, their twisting corridors disorient even the Moblins. Be careful.
        OF_COURSE_YOU_LL_HAVE_TO_PROVE_YOUR                                     = 13352,  -- Of course, you'll have to prove your problem-solving skills during more forgiving operations before we let you tackle the truly scary stuff.
        EACH_EXPEDITION_HAS_A_TOTAL_OF_THREE_GOALS                              = 13353,  -- Each expedition has a total of three goals for you to achieve. Complete just one goal or up to all three--the choice is yours. However, it should go without saying that the more goals you achieve, the better the reward.
        LASTLY_THE_CAVES_ARE_NO_PLACE_FOR_A                                     = 13354,  -- Lastly, the caves are no place for a solo adventurer to be traipsing about. We'll need you to travel in groups of three or more.
        GRIMOIRES_ARE_TYPES_OF_MAGICAL_BOOKS_THAT_ANCIENT                       = 13355,  -- Grimoires are types of magical books that ancient sorcerers brandished in battle long, long ago. Now that they've been unearthed again, we can use them for our benefit.
        WHAT_S_THE_POINT_OF_ADAPTING_THEM_FOR                                   = 13356,  -- What's the point of adapting them for use in the burrows? Why, to record the feats of explorers like you. Without them, it would be much harder to complete expeditions.
        LIKE_I_SAID_THEY_RE_NO_PICTURE_BOOKS                                    = 13357,  -- Like I said, they're no picture books for children. They grant powerful effects for each expedition you finish.
        THESE_BOONS_PACK_A_PUNCH_FROM_THE_GET                                   = 13358,  -- These boons pack a punch from the get-go, but completing expeditions also allows you to increase their potency twice! See, I'm sure these grimoires will prove useful in your studies of the Meebles' tunnels.
        JUST_TO_WARN_YOU_BEFOREHAND_THOUGH_BOONS_THAT                           = 13359,  -- Just to warn you beforehand, though, boons that affect Auto-Reraise and spoils cannot have their potency increased.
        ANOTHER_CATCH_IS_THAT_ONLY_THE_EFFECTS_OF                               = 13360,  -- Another catch is that only the effects of your leader's tome may be bestowed upon your party for normal expeditions. Hopefully that should be all the firepower you need, though.
        AT_THE_MOMENT_WE_ONLY_HAVE_TYPES_OF                                     = 13361,  -- At the moment we only have # types of grimoires available, but we do plan on adding to that number eventually.
        WHEN_YOU_WANT_TO_START_A_NEW_EXPEDITION                                 = 13362,  -- When you want to start a new expedition, just hand over your grimoire to the Burrow Researcher in charge of the burrows you're investigating.
        WHEN_YOU_WANT_TO_START_A_NEW_EXPEDITION_2                               = 13363,  -- When you want to start a new expedition, just hand over your grimoire to me.
        ONCE_YOU_DO_THAT_DOLE_OUT_AND                                           = 13364,  -- Once you do that, [he'll/I'll/I'll] dole out % and %.
        THOSE_RE_THE_ONLY_SUPPLIES_YOU_LL_NEED                                  = 13365,  -- Those're the only supplies you'll need to start spelunking, but not so fast. You first have to decide what expedition you'll undertake.
        I_LL_HELP_YOU_MAKE_THE_NECESSARY_PREPARATIONS                           = 13366,  -- I'll help you make the necessary preparations for that based on your grimoire's records.
        IT_MAY_SEEM_LIKE_A_LOT_TO_HANDLE                                        = 13367,  -- It may seem like a lot to handle, but there's no need to start shaking in your boots. The Burrow Researcher in charge of the burrows you're investigating will help you make all the necessary preparations for that based on your grimoire's records.
        ONLY_THEN_CAN_YOUR_PARTY_LEADER_DECLARE_WHICH                           = 13368,  -- Only then can your party leader declare which journey you and your companions shall embark upon.
        IT_MAY_SMACK_OF_RED_TAPE_BUT_YOU                                        = 13369,  -- It may smack of red tape, but you can only embark upon expedition #1 of each rank at first. At least you're allowed to choose any expedition you've already proven your worth on.
        OH_AND_BEFORE_I_FORGET_FOR_PARTICULARLY_GRUELING                        = 13370,  -- Oh, and before I forget--for particularly grueling endeavors, everyone must sign up individually. The higher-ups like to think of it as exonerating the committee from responsibility or something I don't understand.
        AFTER_SIGNING_UP_YOU_LL_COUGH_ALMOST_COUGH                              = 13371,  -- After signing up, you'll <cough> almost <cough> be ready to set off. The thing is...Meebles[/, like that one over there,/, like that one over there,] roam the mouth of the burrows.
        THEY_DON_T_TRUST_ANYONE_BUT_THE_MOBLINS                                 = 13372,  -- They don't trust anyone but the Moblins, so you'll have to dance like Moblins, prance like Moblins, and even romance like Moblins to gain access to the caves.
        ACTUALLY_YOU_LL_ONLY_NEED_TO_STINK_LIKE                                 = 13373,  -- ...Actually, you'll only need to stink like Moblins. I can give you % in exchange for a grimoire to make sure you smell the part.
        DON_T_WORRY_THIS_METHOD_IS_TRIED_AND                                    = 13374,  -- Don't worry, this method is tried and true. Meebles have very bad eyesight, so they mostly use their sense of smell to determine who's who.
        THAT_SENSE_OF_SMELL_HOWEVER_IS_UNRIVALED_EVEN                           = 13375,  -- That sense of smell, however, is unrivaled. Even if you're the only one who isn't carrying %, they'll sniff you out in an instant.
        IN_FACT_THE_ONLY_REASON_I_HAVEN_T                                       = 13376,  -- In fact, the only reason I haven't been turned into Galka gristle after standing here so long is because I keep one on me at all times.
        ONCE_THE_DOES_ITS_THING_AND_THE_MEEBLES                                 = 13377,  -- Once the % does its thing and the Meebles take you down into their burrows, you're free to experiment all you want.
        OH_BUT_IF_YOU_EVER_LET_ENTHUSIASM_GET                                   = 13378,  -- ...Oh, but if you ever let enthusiasm get the best of you and forget your objectives, just use % to remind yourself.
        THERE_SHOULD_BE_SPELEOLOGICAL_HANDBOOKS_SECRETLY_PLACED_BY              = 13379,  -- There should be Speleological Handbooks secretly placed by our members all over the burrows.
        HOLDING_YOUR_UP_TO_ONE_SHOULD_DO_THE                                    = 13380,  -- Holding your % up to one should do the trick.
        THEY_CAN_ALSO_SERVE_AS_A_WAY_TO                                         = 13381,  -- They can also serve as a way to record your underground activities.
        ONCE_YOU_FINISH_AN_EXPEDITION_ANY_INFORMATION_YOU                       = 13382,  -- Once you finish an expedition, any information you record will have to be reflected in your grimoire.
        YOU_LL_BE_GIVEN_AFTER_COMPLETING_AN_EXPEDITION                          = 13383,  -- You'll be given % after completing an expedition.
        ONE_PUFF_ON_YOUR_WILL_ALLOW_YOUR_WHOLE                                  = 13384,  -- One puff on your % will allow your whole posse to climb back aboveground.
        AFTER_MAKING_YOUR_ESCAPE_THERE_S_ONLY_ONE                               = 13385,  -- After making your escape, there's only one thing left to do. Pay a visit to either the appropriate Burrow Researcher or me and show him your %.
        AFTER_MAKING_YOUR_ESCAPE_YOU_CAN_SHOW_YOUR                              = 13386,  -- After making your escape, you can show your % to me.
        REFERENCE_THE_DATA_YOU_VE_COLLECTED_AND_CATALOG                         = 13387,  -- [One of us will/I'll/I'll] reference the data you've collected and catalog it in your grimoire.
        IF_YOU_EVER_NEED_TO_ESCAPE_BEFORE_COMPLETING                            = 13388,  -- If you ever need to escape before completing an expedition, though, you can always use % instead.
        SADLY_USING_ALLOWS_ONLY_ITS_BEARER_TO_COME                              = 13389,  -- Sadly, using % allows only its bearer to come up for air. Don't forget to show your % once you exit, even if you've bowed out midway through.
        THERE_S_NOTHING_WRONG_WITH_LEAVING_IN_THE                               = 13390,  -- There's nothing wrong with leaving in the middle of an expedition. You'll never be penalized for it, as we wouldn't want to weaken your adventuring spirit.
        OH_AND_IF_YOU_VE_BEEN_WONDERING_HOW                                     = 13391,  -- Oh, and if you've been wondering how to get ahold of one of these %, you'll get one from the Meeble guarding the entrance.
        SOME_SCARY_TWISTED_FIENDS_ROAM_THE_DEPTHS_OF                            = 13392,  -- Some scary, twisted fiends roam the depths of these caverns...at least that's what our scouts who come back alive tell me. Of course, you'll likely come face-to-face with these nightmares, too.
        WHY_WELL_BECAUSE_YOU_LL_BE_TASKED_WITH                                  = 13393,  -- Why? Well, because you'll be tasked with culling one of them after completing the first four expeditions in a course. That's why.
        WHETHER_YOU_CHOOSE_TO_ACCEPT_SUCH_A_DANGEROUS                           = 13394,  -- Whether you choose to accept such a dangerous mission is all up to you. However, keep this in mind.
        ACCEPTING_SUCH_AN_ASSIGNMENT_MEANS_YOU_LL_NEVER                         = 13395,  -- Accepting such an assignment means you'll never get back any grimoires we're holding for you.
        THAT_S_RIGHT_WE_LL_NEED_TO_ARCHIVE                                      = 13396,  -- That's right. We'll need to archive all the precious data you've collected. Jeuno wasn't built in a day, and the same goes for our analysis of Meeble Burrows.
        OH_I_ALMOST_FORGOT_FOR_EXTREMELY_HARROWING_JOURNEYS                     = 13397,  -- Oh, I almost forgot. For extremely harrowing journeys such as these, everyone must sign up individually.
        THIS_WAY_WE_CAN_BE_ABSOLUTELY_SURE_THAT                                 = 13398,  -- This way we can be absolutely sure that everyone's prepared for the task at hand. We wouldn't want people without enough experience getting hurt down there.
        IN_RETURN_FOR_YOUR_COOPERATION_OR_TO_MAKE                               = 13399,  -- In return for your cooperation (or to make sure you truly survive), I'll bestow on your whole party the boons everyone has received up until now.
        THIS_WAY_YOU_LL_ALL_BE_AT_YOUR                                          = 13400,  -- This way you'll all be at your best to face the worst...in the name of science!
        THIS_MAY_SEEM_OBVIOUS_BUT_YOU_CAN_T                                     = 13401,  -- This may seem obvious, but you can't just mull around all you want down there.
        EVEN_IF_YOU_CAN_USE_TO_CONFUSE_THE                                      = 13402,  -- Even if you can use % to confuse the Meebles, they aren't stupid enough to ignore you forever.
        THAT_S_WHY_WE_VE_SET_A_MINUTE                                           = 13403,  -- That's why we've set a #-minute limit per expedition (Earth time). We want to limit the number of casualties to as few as possible. Safety first, that's our motto.
        YOU_SHOULD_ALSO_KNOW_THAT_WE_ONLY_GIVE                                  = 13404,  -- You should also know that we only give out one % every # [hour/minute][/s] (Earth time).
        WE_DO_WANT_YOU_TO_BE_THE_BEST                                           = 13405,  -- We do want you to be the best researcher you can be, though... How about we give you # % as a first-time offer? That way you can learn the ropes faster.
        IT_TOOK_US_A_WHILE_TO_REALIZE_BUT                                       = 13406,  -- It took us a while to realize, but the health of our explorers started failing after they'd carry multiple pouches for long periods of time.
        ON_THE_BRIGHT_SIDE_I_M_BOUND_BY                                         = 13407,  -- On the bright side, I'm bound by the Meeble Burrows Exploration Committee code to keep up to # of them for you. Don't ask why the pouches don't affect me. And if you make a joke about my mother being a Moblin...
        I_MAY_BE_HALER_AND_HEARTIER_THAN_THE                                    = 13408,  -- I may be haler and heartier than the average Galka, but there's only so much of that stench I can take. If you need more pouches than I can carry, you'd better get yourself a pherobarrier box.
        MIND_IF_I_CHANGE_TO_A_FAIRER_SMELLING                                   = 13409,  -- Mind if I change to a fairer smelling subject now?
        IN_THE_EVENT_THAT_THE_SPIRITS_HAUNTING_THESE                            = 13410,  -- In the event that the spirits haunting these caverns disallow one of your brethren entry, just return aboveground within three minutes without completing any objectives. You'll be refunded your % at no cost!
        HOW_NICE_OF_THE_COMMITTEE_RIGHT_NOW_YOU                                 = 13411,  -- How nice of the committee, right? Now you don't have to burst a blood vessel if something happens during your descent.
        WE_MAY_HAVE_MANY_LIMITS_AND_REGULATIONS_BUT                             = 13412,  -- We may have many limits and regulations, but we're not heartless. We also dole out research marks to those who help us learn about Meeble Burrows.
        HOW_DO_YOU_GET_THEM_IT_S_SIMPLE                                         = 13413,  -- How do you get them? It's simple. The more you accomplish down there, the more marks you receive. You can also turn in marks for certain items and equipment.
        THERE_S_NO_NEED_TO_BE_A_FORLORN                                         = 13414,  -- There's no need to be a forlorn funguar, either. The more fellow researchers on your expedition, the more marks you reap. The more the merrier has never rung more true!
        OUR_RESULTS_SUGGEST_THAT_MEEBLES_ARE_RATHER_DOCILE                      = 13415,  -- Our results suggest that Meebles are rather docile creatures, with little if any culture to speak of. They shouldn't pose much of a threat.
        THEY_RE_EASILY_MANIPULATED_THOUGH_AND_THE_MOBLINS_2                     = 13416,  -- They're easily manipulated, though, and the Moblins have taken advantage of that. They put the Meebles to work in caverns all over the realm.
        MEEBLE_BURROWS_MAY_BE_A_QUAINT_NAME_BUT_2                               = 13417,  -- Meeble Burrows may be a quaint name, but what sort of fiends lurk amongst these dank caverns? Why are the Moblins making Meebles do their dirty work? And how large are these underground tunnels anyway? Maybe we haven't learned as much about the Meebles and their habitat as we thought...
        WAIT_IF_YOU_DON_T_MIND_CRAWLING_THROUGH_2                               = 13418,  -- Wait...if you don't mind crawling through caves and dirtying your own hands for a good cause, how about joining in the exploration? We could use another pair of eyes down there. Just talk to me when you decide you'd like to help the scientific community.
        I_M_SURE_I_DON_T_HAVE_TO                                                = 13419,  -- I'm sure I don't have to lecture you on receiving certain boons from your grimoire depending on the expeditions you've completed.
        BUT_YOU_DO_REMEMBER_THAT_BOONS_FROM_ONE                                 = 13420,  -- But you do remember that boons from one grimoire can't be applied to another, right?
        EVEN_WORSE_YOU_BUILD_A_RELATIONSHIP_WITH_YOUR                           = 13421,  -- Even worse, you build a relationship with your grimoire only to have it stolen away from you by some unfeeling bookworms right before you set off to slay the most fearsome of monsters!
        WELL_EVEN_IF_YOU_DON_T_REMEMBER_THOSE                                   = 13422,  -- Well, even if you don't remember, those days are long gone! That's the wonderful thing about science--it progresses!
        WE_VE_IDENTIFIED_UNIQUE_ARCANE_ESSENCES_THAT_ARE                        = 13423,  -- We've identified unique arcane essences that are released with the completion of some goals and imbue the ink of our pens as we record your exploits.
        USING_THESE_ESSENCES_WE_CAN_RECONSTRUCT_THE_BOONS                       = 13424,  -- Using these essences, we can reconstruct the boons you've received from your grimoire records. Let me explain.
        IF_YOU_HAD_COMPLETED_ADJUNCT_EXPEDITION_1_WE                            = 13425,  -- If you had completed Adjunct Expedition #1, we could inscribe the boons from that expedition onto a blank grimoire.
        OF_COURSE_THE_BOON_WOULD_BE_THE_SAME                                    = 13426,  -- Of course the boon would be the same as the one granted from completing that expedition...except for the fact that we can only inscribe level one boons into grimoires. Sorry, but the process is not yet perfect.
        WANT_TO_KNOW_WHAT_ELSE_ISN_T_PERFECT                                    = 13427,  -- Want to know what else isn't perfect? These inscriptions aren't free. It's sad, but grimoires and pheromone sacks don't sprout from the ground, you know!
        MEEBLES_USE_THEIR_LONG_SNIFFERS_TO_SNUFF_UP                             = 13428,  -- Meebles use their long sniffers to snuff up odds and ends from the burrow floor.
        ACCORDING_TO_OUR_LATEST_SCOUTING_REPORT_THEY_DREDGED                    = 13429,  -- According to our latest scouting report, they dredged up some things called... Give me a minute here...
        PALIMPSESTS_I_MAY_NOT_HAVE_THE_BIGGEST_BRAIN                            = 13430,  -- Palimpsests? I may not have the biggest brain this side of the Sea of Shu'Meyo, but I do know that these papers are some powerful stuff.
        THE_MBEC_NOW_ALSO_GIVES_AWAY_WIZENED_WORMS                              = 13431,  -- The MBEC now also gives away wizened worms to adventurers who complete objectives.
        MEEBLES_LOVE_THEIR_WIZENED_WORMS_AND_HOW_QUITE                          = 13432,  -- Meebles love their wizened worms, and how. Quite a non sequitur I pulled on you, right?
        EXCEPT_IT_S_NOT_GIVE_THE_MEEBLES_THAT                                   = 13433,  -- Except it's not! Give the Meebles that guard the burrow entrances some of those water-starved wrigglers and they'll give you stuff in return...possibly even some parades...sorry, palisades...uh, palimpsests.
        RIDICULOUS_NAME_I_KNOW_I_CAN_BARELY_SAY                                 = 13434,  -- Ridiculous name, I know. I can barely say it. These palimpsests are types of magical paper that temporarily aid everyone in your troop.
        ALL_YOU_NEED_TO_DO_IS_TRADE_IT                                          = 13435,  -- All you need to do is trade it to the grimoire inside the caverns and you're good to go.
        I_HAVEN_T_BEEN_ABLE_TO_USE_IT                                           = 13436,  -- I haven't been able to use it myself yet, so this might not be true. Still, a friend of a friend told me that while each piece of parchment has three possible effects, you can only choose one!
        DON_T_WORRY_HE_ASSURES_ME_THAT_YOU                                      = 13437,  -- Don't worry, he assures me that you can choose your desired effect through the wonders of that grimoire down there.
        IF_YOU_WANT_THE_BEAT_EM_UP_POWER                                        = 13438,  -- If you want the beat-'em-up power of all three effects, though, you'll need to gather three pieces of parchment.
        TO_WHERE_WILL_YOU_TRAVEL_THE_SAUROMUGUE_CHAMPAIGN                       = 13439,  -- To where will you travel? The Sauromugue Champaign caverns. The Batallia Downs caverns. Nowhere.
        SO_YOU_WANT_TO_HEAD_TO_THE_CAVERNS                                      = 13440,  -- So, you want to head to the caverns? Alright, I'll make sure you reach Sauromugue Champaign safely...when you're ready, that is.
        SO_YOU_WANT_TO_HEAD_TO_THE_CAVERNS_2                                    = 13441,  -- So, you want to head to the caverns? Alright, I'll make sure you reach Batallia Downs safely...when you're ready, that is.
        WELL_ARE_YOU_READY_READY_AS_EVER_NOT                                    = 13442,  -- Well, are you ready? Ready as ever. Not quite yet.
        IN_THE_MARKET_FOR_A_GRIMOIRE_EH_WHAT                                    = 13443,  -- In the market for a grimoire, eh? What'll it be?
        IN_THE_MARKET_FOR_A_GRIMOIRE_EH_JUST                                    = 13444,  -- In the market for a grimoire, eh? Just so you know, we've finally got some new volumes in stock. Maybe that'll change your decision?
        WHICH_GRIMOIRE_DO_YOU_WANT_NONE_AT_THE                                  = 13445,  -- Which grimoire do you want? None at the moment. %. %. %. %. %.
        I_LL_ACCEPT_EITHER_RESEARCH_MARK_OR_GIL                                 = 13446,  -- I'll accept either # research mark[/s] or # gil for that. So, how'll you pay?
        HOW_WILL_YOU_PAY_I_DON_T_WANT                                           = 13447,  -- How will you pay? I don't want anything anymore. In research marks. (Marks: #) In gil. (Current gil: #)
        UH_YOU_DON_T_HAVE_ENOUGH_TO_BUY                                         = 13448,  -- Uh, you don't have enough [research marks/gil] to buy this...
        RIGHT_I_LL_DOCK_RESEARCH_MARK_FROM_YOUR                                 = 13449,  -- Right, I'll dock # research mark[/s] from your ledger. Here's your %.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_THIS_GIL_S_AUTHENTIC_ALRIGHT                              = 13450,  -- It looks like this # gil's authentic. Alright, here's your %.
        OUR_COFFERS_ARE_EMPTY_WE_DON_T_HAVE                                     = 13451,  -- Our coffers are empty. We don't have anything available for [exchange/purchase].
        OH_SO_YOU_WANT_TO_ABANDON_YOUR_CURRENT                                  = 13452,  -- Oh, so you want to abandon your current expedition?
        BUT_THEN_ALL_THE_DISCOVERIES_YOU_VE_MADE                                = 13453,  -- ...But then all the discoveries you've made during it will be discarded. Is that alright with you?
        HAVE_YOUR_GRIMOIRE_RETURNED_YES_NO                                      = 13454,  -- Have your grimoire returned? Yes. No.
        FINE_BUT_YOU_LL_HAVE_TO_GIVE_ME                                         = 13455,  -- Fine, but you'll have to give me back your %.
        TURNING_IN_YOUR_RESEARCH_MARKS_I_SEE_VERY                               = 13456,  -- Turning in your research marks, I see. Very well. What'll it be?
        WHAT_GOODS_ARE_YOU_LOOKING_FOR_DISPENSABLES_SAUROMUGUE                  = 13457,  -- What goods are you looking for? Dispensables. Sauromugue Champaign rewards. Batallia Downs rewards. Pherobarrier box. None, thanks.
        WHAT_GOODS_ARE_YOU_LOOKING_FOR_ADJUNCT_REWARDS                          = 13458,  -- What goods are you looking for? Adjunct rewards. Assistant rewards. Instructor rewards. Ast. Researcher rewards. Researcher rewards. Researcher Em. rewards. Total completion rewards. None, thanks.
        REDEEM_RESEARCH_MARKS_MARKS_MARKS_MARKS_MARKS_MARKS                     = 13459,  -- Redeem research marks? (Marks: #) % (# marks). % (# marks). % (# marks). % (# marks). % (# marks). % (# marks). % (# marks). % (# marks). % (# marks). Previous page. Next page. Not now.
        WELL_THEN_YOU_LL_NEED_TO_REDEEM_RESEARCH                                = 13460,  -- %? Well then, you'll need to redeem # research mark[/s] for that.
        REDEEM_RESEARCH_MARKS_MARKS_YES_NEVER_MIND                              = 13461,  -- Redeem research marks? (Marks: #) Yes. Never mind.
        REDEEM_RESEARCH_MARKS_MARKS_PAPER_PHEROBARRIER_BOX_MARKS                = 13462,  -- Redeem research marks? (Marks: #) Paper pherobarrier box. (# marks) Wooden pherobarrier box. (# marks) Leather pherobarrier box. (# marks) No.
        A_PHEROBARRIER_BOX_IS_GOING_TO_RUN_YOU                                  = 13463,  -- A [paper/wooden/leather] pherobarrier box is going to run you # marks. Is that okay with you?
        YOU_VE_OBTAINED_A_PHEROBARRIER_BOX_YOU_CAN                              = 13464,  -- You've obtained a [paper/wooden/leather] pherobarrier box! You can now store up to # %!
        YOU_DON_T_HAVE_ENOUGH_MARKS_FOR_THAT                                    = 13465,  -- You don't have enough marks for that... Sorry.
        THE_COMMITTEE_ALSO_SELLS_CERTAIN_KEY_ITEMS_TO                           = 13466,  -- The committee also sells certain key items to adventurers who've completed all expeditions in every rank! So...what'll it be?
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_PURCHASE_GIL_GIL_GIL_GIL                                  = 13467,  -- What will you purchase? (Gil: #) % (# gil). % (# gil). % (# gil). % (# gil). % (# gil). % (# gil). % (# gil). % (# gil). Nothing.
        YOU_DO_KNOW_THE_IS_THE_EMBLEM_OF                                        = 13468,  -- You do know the % is the emblem of valiance for [Adjunct/Assistant/Instructor/Associate Researcher/Researcher] expeditions based in [Sauromugue Champaign/Batallia Downs], right? Are you sure that's the one you want?
        PURCHASE_THE_YES_NO                                                     = 13469,  -- Purchase the %? Yes. No.
